ons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I plan on questing for Ro once it becomes feasible for me to do so, but between then and now, is there anything I should look out for?<br><br>I especially want to get some better boots (and better-looking) than Banded, since it just clashes with my otherwaise all-black outfit. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I'm currently level 25 and hunting in LOIO. (If I can play for any decent length of time, I should be levelling pretty quickly; great exp)<br><br>You can view my profile here:<br><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=96231">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=96231</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><br>Thanks.<br>/salute<br> <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=96231">-Occam</a><br>Paladin of Tunare<br>24th Crusade<br>Followers of Nobility<br>Zebuxoruk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utiriantrueblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tirian Trueblade</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/iconsg.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 426<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/8/02 5:38:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=173.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/tirianicon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mid-twenties armor</span><hr size=1> Prices on various lower level armor sets (I'm thinking of all sets below Deepwater and the Velious quest sets) have dropped so much that you can easily afford them before you could obtain them by hunting or questing for them.  Ro is a prime example.  The BP of Ro requires you to camp the Kitchen in Mistmoore, which is no easy feat for a group in their low 30s.  The Greaves require you kill a named Hill Giant in West Commons, I could go on.  <br><br>Don't get me wrong, I had a blast questing for Ro armor, but that was back before Velious, and Deepwater armor was selling for a mint, compared to 500pp for many pieces nowadays.  Now with the advent of Crusty, Ry'Gorr, Fine Plate, and the amount of Ro for sale at your local auction zone, you will be able to buy a much better set of armor than you could hope to loot or quest for yourself.<br><br>There isn't much between BA and Ro really, except for the sets I've already mentioned, at least no sets I can think of off the top of my head at the moment, but I'd imagine you could start to afford pieces from any of those sets fairly soon, perhaps not all at once, but certinally one piece at a time.  <br><br>My advice would be to take a look at the sets as a whole, since it seems you want to have matching pieces, and then choose the set that you can best afford, or best fits your needs.  If you really like black, you can get Fine Plate dyed black for you. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br>Just my two cents. <p><img src= "http://home.earthlink.net/~asercion/tirsigns.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=occam>Occam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/8/02 8:34:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=173.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mid-twenties armor</span><hr size=1> Well, it's not so much that each piece must be of the same type; it just has to go together. A Paladin should look GOOD while slaying the undead! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I like questing, so I'll probably end up going for Ro eventually.  (I even did the Falchion of the Koada'Vie quest after I had my Ghoulbane <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br><br>But I won't worry about it too much until then.<br><br>Thanks for your advice. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=96231">-Occam</a><br>Paladin of Tunare<br>24th Crusade<br>Followers of Nobility<br>Zebuxoruk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvenjonexi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VENJONEXI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/11/02 1:39:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=173.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mid-twenties armor</span><hr size=1> Here are just a couple of suggestions which arent too costly for upgrades:<br>Face: Cougar skin mask quest <br>If your higher lvl buddy can free up some time and take you to iceclad w/ 2 mammoth meats (from anywhere) and I believe 2 med qual cougar skins you can get a the mask by turning them in to quest giver (see Allakhazams Magical realm for more details) ac6 +2 dex / agi +10 hp<br>Finger: Jagged Bands +5 ac +3 str go to ec they go for 20-30 p a piece <br>Hands: Dark mail guantlets +10 ac +5 dex +50 mana <br> bought mine for 100p in my early 20's used them until late 30's when i bought my Gauntlets of the Black<br>Chest: Dusty Bp +22 ac +5 sta +20 hp usually go for about 200p <br>Tattered Mantle or Crested Spaulders both usually go for a couple of hundred plat and are great upgrades you could keep for a very long time.<br>Some things to go for in your 30's:<br>Hero bracer +9 ac +10 str +5 sv poi/dis - quested<br>Save up for Gauntlets of the Black +15 ac +4 str +3 wis<br>Ro greaves - quested or save up for Crustacean Shell legs the dex hit (-4) is kind of big but the +16 sta more than makes up for it.<br>Feet: save up for crustacean shell boots instead of Ro they are lower ac but the Sta makes up for the hp diff and ac diff IMOHP.  Not to mention both pieces have str stat as well.  <br>Also save up for Ry'gorr neckguard / fire opal wedding bands (ac / hp rings - crafted and a bit costly)<br>and DW gear.  <br><br>Venjonexi Bloodmoon<br>38th Paladin of Tunare <br>The Rathe <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showPrevMessage?topicID=173.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showNextMessage?topicID=173.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=173.topic&index=3><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.emailToFriend?topicID=173.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.threadControl?topicID=173.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><